wikipedia_page.main: Kimberley Woods (born 8 September 1995) is a British slalom canoeist who has competed at the international level since 2011.She won seven medals at the ICF Canoe Slalom World Championships with four golds (C1 team: 2017, 2018, K1 team: 2019, 2021), a silver (K1 team: 2015) and two bronzes (K1: 2021, K1 team: 2018). She has also won eleven medals (8 golds, 1 silver and 2 bronzes) at the European Championships.She has qualified to represent Great Britain at the 2020 Summer Olympics in Tokyo in the Women's K1 event where she finished in 10th place.
